-- Milan Prosecutors Probing Telecom Italia on False Phone Card Sales Data
-- Elisa Martinuzzi
-- 2010-07-01T09:22:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/telecom-italia-probed-in-milan-for-false-mobile-phone-card-sales-data.html

          
          
             Telecom Italia SpA is under probe in
Milan for manipulating mobile phone sales data, according to an
e-mailed statement from Italy’s finance police.  
 The country’s finance police also fined Telecom Italia 1.14
million euros for privacy violations, the statement said. A
spokeswoman for the company didn’t have an immediate comment.
Italy’s police is also probing 30 dealers for forging sales of
phone cards, it said.  
          
          


  


        